## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 7 â€” Trimming Low Quality Reads (Markdown)**

```markdown
# âœ‚ï¸ Step 2: Read Trimming (Trim Galore)

We remove adapters and low-quality bases.

This step improves:
- Mapping accuracy
- Variant calling reliability
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 8 â€” Run Trim Galore (Code)**

```python
!mkdir trimmed_reads

!TrimGalore-0.6.7/trim_galore --paired dataset/sample_R1.fastq.gz dataset/sample_R2.fastq.gz -o trimmed_reads
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 9 â€” Mapping to Reference Genome (Markdown)**

```markdown
# ðŸ—º Step 3: Map Reads to Reference Genome

We use **BWA-MEM** for alignment:
- Fast
- Accurate
- Suitable for WGS data
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 10 â€” Mapping (Code)**

```python
# Index reference genome
!bwa index Genomics_learning_workshop/reference/your_reference.fasta

# Map reads
!bwa mem Genomics_learning_workshop/reference/your_reference.fasta \
    trimmed_reads/sample_R1_val_1.fq.gz \
    trimmed_reads/sample_R2_val_2.fq.gz \
    > sample.sam
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 11 â€” SAM to BAM, Sort, Index (Code)**

```python
# Convert SAM to BAM
!samtools view -bS sample.sam > sample.bam

# Sort BAM
!samtools sort sample.bam -o sample.sorted.bam

# Index BAM
!samtools index sample.sorted.bam
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 12 â€” Variant Calling (Markdown)**

```markdown
# ðŸ§¬ Step 4: Variant Calling (bcftools)

This step identifies:
- SNPs
- Small indels
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 13 â€” Variant Calling (Code)**

```python
# Variant calling pipeline
!bcftools mpileup -Ou -f Genomics_learning_workshop/reference/your_reference.fasta sample.sorted.bam \
 | bcftools call -mv -Oz -o raw_variants.vcf.gz

# Index VCF
!bcftools index raw_variants.vcf.gz
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 14 â€” Variant Filtering (Markdown)**

```markdown
# ðŸ§¼ Step 5: Variant Filtering

We apply basic filters:
- Minimum depth (DP)
- Quality score (QUAL)
- Genotype quality (GQ)
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 15 â€” Variant Filtering (Code)**

```python
!bcftools filter -i 'DP>5 && QUAL>30' raw_variants.vcf.gz -o filtered_variants.vcf
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 16 â€” PCA Preparation (Markdown)**

```markdown
# ðŸ“Š Step 6: PCA for Population Structure

We convert VCF â†’ PLINK format and visualize genetic variation using PCA.
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 17 â€” PCA (Code)**

```python
# Convert to PLINK
!plink --vcf filtered_variants.vcf --make-bed --out genotype_data

# Run PCA
!plink --bfile genotype_data --pca --out pca_results
```

---

## ðŸ“˜ **CELL 18 â€” Plot PCA (Code)**

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Load PCA result
df = pd.read_csv("pca_results.eigenvec", sep="\s+", header=None)
df.columns = ["Sample", "PC1", "PC2"]

plt.scatter(df["PC1"], df["PC2"])
plt.xlabel("PC1")
plt.ylabel("PC2")
plt.title("PCA Plot")
plt.show()
```

